                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Here follows a list of articles on United States international economic activity
                    arising from the accelerating United States defense effort, based on the
                    Department of State’s classified weekly publication, <hi rend="italic">Current
                        Economic Developments</hi>, a document “designed to highlight developments
                    in the economic divisions of the Department of State, and to indicate the
                    economic problems which are currently receiving attention in the Department.”
                    (The first issue for the year, January 2, 1951, is No. 286.)</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">January 8, 1951 (No. 287):</p>
                <p>
                    <list>
                        <item>“Economic Effects of Mobilization in the United States” (<ref
                                target="#pg_1">p. 1</ref>)</item>
                        <item>“Rubber Supply Problems and Proposed Actions” (<ref target="#pg_4">p.
                                4</ref>)</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">January 15, 1951 (No. 288):</p>
                <p>
                    <list>
                        <item>“International Raw Materials Machinery” (<ref target="#pg_4">p.
                                4</ref>)</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">January 22, 1951 (No. 289):</p>
                <p>
                    <list>
                        <item>“Committee Created on Foreign Supplies and Requirements” (<ref
                                target="#pg_3">p. 3</ref>)</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">January 29, 1951 (No. 290):</p>
                <p>
                    <list>
                        <item>“International Commodity Groups to be Established” (<ref
                                target="#pg_1">p. 1</ref>)</item>
                        <item>“US Price Controls Apply to Exports and Imports” (<ref target="#pg_2"
                                >p. 2</ref>)</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">February 19, 1951 (No. 293):</p>
                <p>
                    <list>
                        <item>“Demands Increase on US for Wheat” (<ref target="#pg_8">p.
                            8</ref>)</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
